She has served on 7 public, 3 private, and numerous non profit boards.

Jaynie’s board service leverages 30 years of line operating, P&L experience in C-suite positions. She was the EVP and top executive responsible for Retail & Business Banking at First Interstate of California and two other major financial institutions during the era of deregulation, growth, and consolidation. Next Jaynie was the COO for public Overture Services Inc the creator of paid search and pioneer in what is now the $60 billion SEM (search engine marketing) industry. Overture grew from $100 million to $1.2 billion in profitable revenues in three years. She began her career in management consulting working for Booz, Allen.

Jaynie's current public boards are EXL Service, Core Logic, funds for WAMCO, and Pacific Premier Bancorp. For non profits, Jaynie is chair and a long time board member for Pasadena’s Huntington Hospital, prior chair and board member for Flintridge Preparatory School, and a co-founder and board member for 0026bf40-8f42-87e2-b371-978055165959,,Josh,Elman,Josh Elman,,40349,,joshe,fIkrex6pSbSSd1Ooo4Lbmg==,,False,,,,,False,,True,False,Product Builder,,"Product leader focused on disruptive products that change the way people interact and communicate with each other and discover new information. I like playing with the latest and greatest technology, but my greatest thrills come from applying that into new situations where anyone can use it without understanding the tech. You know you've succeeded when your neighbors tell you about the latest thing they've discovered... and you've worked on it. Most important to me is finding an amazing group of talented people to share the journey with.

I have been lucky to be a part of several of the most significant internet and social companies and led or was involved in key projects that have altered their trajectories including early product and platform roles at LinkedIn, Facebook, and Twitter. I led the product, marketing, and design teams at Robinhood as we more than doubled the userbase, revenue, and the team.

I've also spent many years at Greylock as a General Partner where I led investments and served on the board of the next wave of social products including Discord, Musical.ly (now Tiktok), Medium, and
